<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/index.php?title=Blastclaw&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Overview">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>This ship is ubiquitous escorting Pirate freighters and operating as the core of a hunting pack. They will quite frequently chase down your freighters and sometimes they'll even start picking on stations. Since they usually come bundled with <a href="/index.php/Plasma_Burst_Generator" title="Plasma Burst Generator">Plasma Burst Generators</a>, this ship usually poses a very dangerous threat even when alone and outclassed, and should be engaged with extreme caution.
</p><p>The Blastclaw should really be classed as an M3+.  Its cost and overall performance put it in this bracket even if it's "officially" designated an M3. The major drawback is that it has less gun mounts on the front compared to other M3s, although it hardly matters since it has compatibility with certain powerful guns such as the aforementioned <a href="/index.php/Plasma_Burst_Generator" title="Plasma Burst Generator">Plasma Burst Generator</a> and the <a href="/index.php/Mass_Driver" title="Mass Driver">Mass Driver</a>.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/index.php?title=Blastclaw&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The product of rare collaboration between two pirate clans, the Blastclaw is a distinctive and destructive ship that should be kept at a safe distance.
</p><p>One of the new breed of purpose-built pirate vessels aimed at countering the increasing threat from <a href="/index.php/Commonwealth" title="Commonwealth">Commonwealth</a> military patrols, the Blastclaw offers pirate crews some much-needed heavy fighter support when engaging enemy forces.  Like its big brother the <a href="/index.php/Carrack" title="Carrack">Carrack</a>, the Blastclaw trades forward firepower for improved turret coverage.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Variants">Variants</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/index.php?title=Blastclaw&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Variants">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Blastclaw">Blastclaw</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/index.php?title=Blastclaw&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Blastclaw">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>It is unusually powerful for a Pirate craft, actually having balanced overall performance, on par or better than an average M3.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Blastclaw_Prototype">Blastclaw Prototype</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/index.php?title=Blastclaw&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Blastclaw Prototype">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>A marked improvement over the original, the main attraction of the Blastclaw Prototype is its 650 unit cargobay, allowing it to be used as a combat-capable tanker for larger craft or as a missile gunship. This makes it the fighter with the second largest cargo bay in the game after the Enhanced version of the <a href="/index.php/Kea" title="Kea">Teladi Kea</a>, which beats it only by 100 more bays. It can mount an additional 25MJ shield and can move more quickly. Combining these features with its wide payload options makes it one of the best <a href="/index.php/M3" title="M3">M3</a> ships available.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Physical_Characteristics">Physical Characteristics</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/index.php?title=Blastclaw&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Physical Characteristics">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The Blastclaw, like most Pirate-designed ships, looks like it was put together from spare parts and has the ubiquitous red-and-yellow paint scheme.  It is a rather stocky ship, presenting more of a top profile than most fighters but average from other angles.  Turret coverage is likewise fairly standard for the <a href="/index.php/M3%2B" title="M3+">M3+</a> class, with front and rear turrets each covering 180 degrees.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Combat">Combat</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/index.php?title=Blastclaw&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Combat">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>When equipped with <a href="/index.php/Plasma_Burst_Generator" title="Plasma Burst Generator">PBGs</a>, the Blastclaw can wreak extraordinary havoc on any target, including <a href="/index.php/Category:Capital_Ships" title="Category:Capital Ships">capital ships</a>. With a more standard weapons array, it is still nevertheless a respectable dogfighter.  With 2x2 turrets it can even function as a light corvette, circling its target while the turrets throw <a href="/index.php/Phased_Repeater_Gun" title="Phased Repeater Gun">PRG</a> at it or any enemy fighters that get in the way.
</p>
