<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Availability">Availability</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/index.php?title=Blastclaw&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Availability">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Available as one of many <a href="/index.php/Ownerless_ships" title="Ownerless ships">Ownerless ships</a>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Suggested_Roles">Suggested Roles</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/index.php?title=Blastclaw&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Suggested Roles">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>While the Blastclaw is a deadly fighter in any capacity the high cost and relative rarity make it best used as a player ship or personal wingman. The Prototype variant is an excellent mission ship as it has enough firepower to rapidly dispatch anything smaller than an <a href="/index.php/M7" title="M7">M7</a> and its cavernous cargo bay allows one to carry copious amounts of energy cells for roaming the galaxy while still having space left over for taxi missions.
</p>
